The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, June 2 (PTI) The Reserve Bank of India has asked banks to reframe cheque collection to avoid delays in clearances and has given them a month to act on the matter.           
	The RBI has asked the lenders to reframe policies so that credit and debit for local cheques should be given on the same or next day of their presentation for clearing.                   
	 Mumbai (PTI): Senior lawyer Abbas Kazmi, who represents 26/11 prime accused Ajmal Kasab, will be paid Rs 2,500 by the Maharashtra government for each days work. The case is heard five days every week, entitling Kazmi to Rs 12,500 per week or Rs 50,000 monthly for defending Kasab, officials said.                   
	 London (PTI): An NRI doctor in the UK, held guilty of sexually assaulting two women patients during their medical check-ups, has been ordered to do 80 hours of unpaid community work even as he faces cancellation of his license to practice. Rajinder Aggarwal, 54, is expected to be struck-off the medical register by the General Medical Council.                                                                                                                           
